Vice President Kamala Harris visited Claflin University in Orangeburg, South Carolina to engage in a conversation with student leaders about their priorities for the nation and the world. She highlighted the importance of college as a phase of life where individuals develop and decide who they are in relation to the world and their nation. Harris also discussed the impact of young voters in the 2020 election and the issues they prioritize, such as affordable college education, Pell Grants, investments in HBCUs and minority-serving institutions, climate change, and the racial wealth gap. She emphasized the need to address mental health, particularly among college students, and called for better healthcare policies in the country. Secretary of Education Miguel Cardona also spoke at the event.